				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${{\rm{CH}}}_{{\rm{3}}}{\rm{CN}}+hv\to \bullet {\rm{CN}}+\bullet {{\rm{CH}}}_{{\rm{3}}}$$\end{document}Subsequent abstraction of a proton from ACN, or in our case from a molecule of water, furnishes the HCN molecule.

Following the production of HCN, the generation of FA follows a well-understood mechanism49. Addition of a hydroxyl radical followed by rapid tautomeric rearrangement leads to the FA radical.•OH+HCN→•NCHOH→•OCHNH\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
